gstack (redact-engine)
  License: MIT
  Description: A redaction engine that normalizes text (NFKC + zero-width /
    bidi strip) before matching secret/PII patterns, defeating
    Unicode-confusable evasion, with a fail-closed input cap.
  Used in: skills/incident/scripts/redact-engine.py (#5987)
  Portions adopted: The "normalize-before-match" adversary model
    (NFKC + invisible-character strip ahead of pattern matching) and the
    ReDoS-safe input-cap / synthetic-HIGH fail-closed posture. No source
    code was copied verbatim (clean-room): the Soleur implementation is a
    fresh Python 3 rewrite behind a contract-preserving `redact-sentinel.sh`
    shim, ports Soleur's own 14+ secret/PII classes with `re.ASCII` C-locale
    semantics, matches over a WHOLE-STRING NFKC normalization (no
    per-codepoint offset-map, which would be a fail-open), and re-checks the
    byte cap AFTER NFKC expansion. The upstream in-place-rewrite behavior is
    intentionally NOT carried over — the Soleur sentinel halts, it never
    rewrites.

